{"eventId":"evt_fake_drug_002","eventType":"claim_softened","claimId":"clm_xano_001","fromRevisionId":999000003,"toRevisionId":999000004,"section":"Efficacy","before":"A Phase II trial (NCT-FAKE-023, n=320) of Xanoleptin 50 mg/day reported a mean reduction of 12.4 points on the Hamilton Depression Rating Scale (HAM-D) versus 4.2 for placebo (p < 0.001). Pharmaficta Corp described the results as 'transformative' in its 2021 press release.","after":"Early Phase II results (NCT-FAKE-023, n=320) initially reported a mean HAM-D reduction of 12.4 points versus 4.2 for placebo (p < 0.001). A subsequent larger Phase III trial (NCT-FAKE-045, n=1,200) found a HAM-D reduction of 8.1 points versus 4.0 for placebo (p < 0.01). Following an FDA warning letter regarding promotional claims, Pharmaficta removed the term 'transformative' from its marketing materials.","deterministicFacts":[{"fact":"The Phase III trial results (8.1 point reduction, n=1,200) were added alongside the original Phase II claim.","detail":"The larger trial showed a smaller effect, consistent with regression to the mean in a larger sample."},{"fact":"The FDA warning letter and removal of 'transformative' language were documented.","detail":"FDA Warning Letter reference: FAKE-WL-2023-045, dated 2023-08-22."}],"modelInterpretation":{"semanticChange":"Softened the efficacy claim by incorporating the smaller Phase III effect and documenting the FDA's rejection of promotional language.","confidence":0.91,"policyDimension":"scientific_accuracy","discussionType":"evidence_update"},"layer":"observed","timestamp":"2023-09-15T14:30:00Z"}
